To say 2022 was a tumultuous year for me is an understatement. When I reflect back to NYE last year, it’s insane to think about the stark contrast of how the year began versus how it’s ending. 2022 was definitely a year filled with many new, unique challenges and life transitions. I won’t deny that it was often confusing, frustrating, and emotionally draining. Relationships ended. Friendships were tested. Careers changed. There were new ways to living to adapt to. 

But there was also much positivity to come out of 2022 as well. Goals (even some that felt nearly impossible to reach) were achieved. New opportunities were presented.  There was a multitude of exciting experiences; from film festivals to concerts to unforgettable nights out to traveling to exploring new places and everything in between. Through it all, I got to cross paths and experience these things with some incredible folks. Whether you’re a long time friend, new friend, colleague, we’ve spoken in passing, or I’ve shot photos for you, you’ve all made this year a memorable one and made the challenges easier to navigate. ❤️ (I’m not gonna tag everyone, but you know who you are).

Anyway, enough of the long winded, sappy post. 

📸 🌇 Here’s yet another sunset shot from one of my favorite docks in NYC, to commemorate the sun setting for one last time this year.

Show me something more Philly than the Mummers Parade and a birds game taking place at the exact same time in South Philly.

I ran my first half marathon yesterday (actually, first race ever for that matter) and today is #MedalMonday, so I figured I’d join in on the fun!

This is a HUGE personal victory for me; a little over a year ago, I made some serious changes and adopted a much healthier lifestyle. In that process, I lost 50lbs, developed a much better relationship with food, and….picked up running. Which is funny, because I absolutely used to abhor running and begrudgingly only did it when necessary. Fast forward to January 2023, a friend/colleague of mine encouraged me to sign up for the Brooklyn Half Marathon with them. I thought they were insane, but they put me up to the challenge. And now here we are!

What an incredible, magical night of music with @baconbrosmusic and the wickedly talented students of @rock2future at World Cafe for the 2023 Music For All Ball. 

Rock to the Future does a myriad of amazing things for Philly youth and last night was about highlighting all the transformational work they’ve done and continue to do on a daily basis. 

It’s also awe-inspiring seeing Michael and Kevin (who were also once music students in Philly) returning to their roots to give back and mentor a future generation.
